<h1>React Rails Client Side Only Rendering</h1>
<p>
  This example demonstrates client side only rendering.<br/><br/>
  The source HTML of this page will only show a DIV with an ID matching HelloWorld.<br/>
  <pre>
    <%= "<div id=\"HelloWorld-react-component-0\"></div>" %>
  </pre><br/><br/>
  Compare this to the HTML created for server rendering.<br/>
</p>

<hr/>
<h2>Setup</h2>
<ol>
  <li>
    Create component source: spec/dummy/client/app/components/HelloWorld.jsx
  </li>
  <li>
    Expose the HelloWorld Component: spec/dummy/client/app/startup/clientGlobals.jsx
    <br/>
    <pre>
      import HelloWorld from '../components/HelloWorld';
      window.HelloWorld = HelloWorld;
    </pre>
  </li>
  <li>
    Place the component on the view: spec/dummy/app/views/pages/client_side_hello_world.html.erb
    <br/>
    <pre>
      <%% react_component("HelloWorld", @app_props_server_render, prerender: false, trace: true, generator_function: false) %>
    </pre>
  </li>
</ol>

